== Alignment Output ==

As in [[SeqIO|Bio.SeqIO]], there is a single output function '''Bio.AlignIO.write()'''.  This takes three arguments: some alignments, a file handle to write to, and the format to use.

As of Biopython 1.48, the alignment object acquired a '''format()''' method to give a string containing the alignment in the specified file format, e.g.

<source lang=python>
AlignIO.read(open("PF09395_seed.sth"), "stockholm")
print alignment.format("fasta")
</source>

